element.name: Mary Love's Mid-life Crisis by Mary Love, Traditional Cache (1.5/1.5)
element.description: Mary Love's angst will be dispelled if you find this cache.
element.long-description: Traditional cache located in the in the Spricklestown area overlooking Ballymacarney between the Ward Cross and Hollystown.
element.encoded-hints: Don't think you've found salvation, Or that the day is won, When you reach your destination, The journey's just begun.

ul.li:
2010-05-04T19:00:00Z : Didn't find it by Drea-Popa
We were looking for this cache on our way to the airport. Unfortunately we couldn't find this cache...

2010-01-31T20:00:00Z : Didn't find it by CluelessTwo
We were in a bit of a hurry this morning as we were planning to cache our way back up north. So it was a 10 minute look and then we gave up. We did see the toys people chated about but the garmin was pointing into the field to a place that was just a bit of field with no where to hide anything. We searched where we thought it should be but this one stumped us, which was very annoying and a bad start to our day.
[This entry was edited by CluelessTwo on Sunday, January 31, 2010 at 3:30:42 PM.]

2009-10-18T19:00:00Z : Found it by Blue Jay 59
Found the Mary's Mid-Life crisis cache on a Sunday afternoon run around. Hope Mary is feeling better ;) Took Autism geocoin.Left Blue bead necklace. TFTC. Eily & Mot.

Found it good hint
